2019 Women's World Cup Predictions

Soccer Power Index (SPI) ratings and chances of advancing for every team
Forecast from before 3rd group matches

Source: FiveThirtyEight

Raw data: wwc_forecasts.csv

library(reactable)
library(htmltools)

forecasts <- read.csv("wwc_forecasts.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
forecasts <- forecasts[, c("team", "group", "spi", "global_o", "global_d", "group_1", 
                           "group_2", "group_3", "make_round_of_16", "make_quarters", 
                           "make_semis", "make_final", "win_league", "points")]

pct_formatter <- function(zero_dash = FALSE) {
  function(value) {
    if (zero_dash && value == 0) "  \u2013 "  # en dash
    else if (value == 1) "\u2713"  # checkmark
    else if (value < 0.01) " <1%"
    else if (value > 0.99) ">99%"
    else formatC(paste0(round(value * 100), "%"), width = 4)
  }
}

get_rating_color <- function(x, bias = 1) {
  rgb <- colorRamp(c("#ff2700", "#f8fcf8", "#44ab43"), bias = bias)(x)
  sprintf("rgb(%s)", paste(rgb, collapse = ","))
}

get_knockout_color <- function(x) {
  rgb <- colorRamp(c("#ffffff", "#fdffeb", "#a6dbad", "#35b0ab"))(x)
  rgb <- colorRamp(c("#ffffff", "#e2f6c1", "#74c5aa", "#35b0ab"), bias = 1.6)(x)
  rgb <- colorRamp(c("#ffffff", "#f2fbd2", "#c9ecb4", "#93d3ab", "#35b0ab"), bias = 2)(x)
  # rgb <- colorRamp(c("#fdffeb", "#f0fbcf", "#93d3ab", "#35b0ab"), bias = 2)(x)
  # rgb <- colorRamp(c("#f2fbd2", "#c9ecb4", "#93d3ab", "#35b0ab"), bias = 2)(x)
  
  
  
  sprintf("rgb(%s)", paste(rgb, collapse = ","))
}

rating_col <- function(maxWidth = 45, ...) {
  # todo put color in here
  colDef(format = colFormat(digits = 1), 
         maxWidth = maxWidth, align = "center", class = "cell number", ...)
}

group_stage_col <- function(class = NULL, ...) {
  colDef(cell = pct_formatter(zero_dash = TRUE), maxWidth = 70, align = "center", 
         class = paste("number", class), ...)
}

knockout_stage_col <- function(maxWidth = 70, class = NULL, ...) {
  colDef(
    cell = pct_formatter(zero_dash = FALSE), 
    maxWidth = maxWidth, 
    class = paste("number", class), 
    style = function(value) {
      if (value < 0.01) {
        list(color = "#aaa")
      } else {
        list(color = "#111", background = get_knockout_color(value))
      }
    },
    ...
  )
}

tbl <- reactable(
  forecasts,
  pagination = FALSE,
  defaultSorted = "win_league",
  columnGroups = list(
    colGroup(
      "Team Rating", 
      c("spi", "global_o", "global_d"),
      headerClass = "group-header"
    ),
    colGroup(
      "Chance of Finishing Group Stage In ...", 
      c("group_1", "group_2", "group_3"),
      headerClass = "group-header"
    ),
    colGroup(
      "Knockout Stage Chances", 
      c("make_round_of_16", "make_quarters", "make_semis", "make_final", "win_league"),
      headerClass = "group-header"
    )
  ),
  defaultColDef = colDef(
    headerClass = "header", 
    defaultSortOrder = "desc",
    style = JS("
      function(rowInfo, state) {
        if (state.sorted.length > 0 && state.sorted[0].id === 'group') {
          const group = rowInfo.row.group
          const nextRow = state.sortedData[rowInfo.viewIndex + 1]
          if (nextRow && group !== nextRow.group) {
            return { boxShadow: '0 2px 0 #555' }
          }
        }
      }
    ")
  ),
  columns = list(
    team = colDef(
      defaultSortOrder = "asc",
      headerStyle = list(fontWeight = 700), 
      cell = function(value, index) {
        div(
          class = "team",
          img(class = "flag", src = sprintf("images/%s.png", value)),
          div(class = "team-name", value),
          div(class = "record", sprintf("%s pts.", forecasts[index, "points"]))
        )
      }
    ),
    group = colDef(defaultSortOrder = "asc", align = "center", maxWidth = 80, 
                   class = "group", headerStyle = list(fontWeight = 700)),
    spi = rating_col(maxWidth = 55),
    global_o = rating_col(name = "Off.", cell = function(value) {
      scaled <- (value - min(forecasts$global_o)) / (max(forecasts$global_o) - min(forecasts$global_o))
      color <- get_rating_color(scaled, bias = 1.3)
      value <- format(round(value, 1), nsmall = 1)
      div(class = "spi-rating", style = list(background = color), value)
    }),
    global_d = rating_col(name = "Def.", defaultSortOrder = "asc", cell = function(value) {
      scaled <- 1 - (value - min(forecasts$global_d)) / (max(forecasts$global_d) - min(forecasts$global_d))
      color <- get_rating_color(scaled, bias = 0.6)
      value <- format(round(value, 1), nsmall = 1)
      div(class = "spi-rating", style = list(background = color), value)
    }),
    group_1 = group_stage_col(name = "1st Place", class = "border-left"),
    group_2 = group_stage_col(name = "2nd Place"),
    group_3 = group_stage_col(name = "3rd Place"),
    make_round_of_16 = knockout_stage_col(name = "Make Round of 16", class = "border-left"),
    make_quarters = knockout_stage_col(name = "Make Qtr-Finals"),
    make_semis = knockout_stage_col(name = "Make Semifinals", maxWidth = 85),
    make_final = knockout_stage_col(name = "Make Final"),
    win_league = knockout_stage_col(name = "Win World Cup"),
    points = colDef(show = FALSE)
  ),
  highlight = FALSE,
  borderless = TRUE,
  class = "standings-table"
)

div(class = "standings",
  div(class = "title",
    h2("2019 Women's World Cup Predictions"),
    "Soccer Power Index (SPI) ratings and chances of advancing for every team"
  ),
  tbl,
  "Forecast from before 3rd group matches"
)
